4Geeks Academy offers a Cybersecurity Bootcamp for individuals who want to become cybersecurity specialists and protect the digital future. The program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills to secure these environments. Participants will learn about cloud security, penetration testing (both offensive and defensive), and cyber threat intelligence analysis. The program also covers managing risks using data loss prevention (DLP) strategies and compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST. The bootcamp lasts for 16 weeks and includes 3 live online classes per week. The class size is limited to 16 people. Upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate recognized by multiple institutions. No previous experience is required. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560. For more information, visit the website at https://4geeksacademy.com/us/coding-bootcamps/cybersecurity. stop